<subsection xml:id="subsec-Relating-interrior-angles-to-the-number-of-sides-of-a-polygon">
            <title>Relating interrior angles to the number of sides of a polygon</title>
            <p>                          
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            If a polygon has n sides, the number of triangles is <m>n-2</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The sum of the interior angles in a polygon = number of triangles <m>\times 180^\circ</m>                                                                
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            <me>180^\circ\times (n-2) </me>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            To get the size of one interior angle in a regular polygon, divide the sum of the interior angles by the number of sides.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>\frac{90^\circ\times (2n-4)}{n}=\frac{180^\circ\times (n-2)}{n} </me>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            
</subsection>